                <h1>Starburst Candy: A Chewy Delight of Flavor</h1>
                <p>Starburst candy, known for its chewy texture and vibrant flavors, was first introduced in the UK in 1960 as "Opal Fruits." The candy quickly gained popularity and made its way to the U.S. in 1967. Today, Starburst comes in various fruit flavors, making it a favorite treat for many. Its bright packaging and delicious taste continue to charm candy lovers around the world.</p>
